image_desc: Photo by Sharon Teh on November 25, 2020. May be an image of drink.
text:
#TBT to the pseudo farewell this crazy bunch threw for me in September.

My last image of the night was this fantastic Coffee Brandy, surprisingly from Malaysia ! Lots of drinks in between. An aged 30 year old Brandy as the night wore on, after the wine we had during dinner,  with Negronis pre dinner.

Decent Mexican grub in the East.
Highlights for us were the Fish Tacos and the beautifully presented Baby Octopus. Of course you can never go wrong with the Shrimp Pasta too.

But oh, what fun. Would have been a right total blast with the full gang, but just 5 pax for CB Phase 2 ğŸ¤·. 

Always so much to talk and jest with this bunch that I stumbled home close to 4am. 
There's an idea - I need more fortification to get through the sleepless nights nursing Kimi ğŸ˜‰.

After falling in love with sensory play, I decided to introduce S to numbers and shapes the fun way! I havenâ€™t been a big fan of Mathematics myself so I could not bring myself to teach her through the pen and paper method! Besides she was too young! Hence sensory play was the answer! ğŸ˜€

Since rice left a big mess, I decided to give chickpeas a shot! I purchased these pretty rainbow chickpeas from @5littlesense5. I threw in some numbers and shapes counters which I had purchased on shoppee earlier(link below). We would identify the numbers and shapes and place them in a container! Then we would also have a mini â€œtreasure huntâ€ to make it more interactive for S. At times, to be in control of the play, she would  request to include other â€œtoysâ€ like toy eggs! ğŸ˜‚ I would allow that! Every play would be flexible and Iâ€™hd let her make decisions to promote independent play! We had lots of fun..most importantly we created beautiful memories! â¤ï¸

Circuit Breakers These are put on individual stocks (equity & derivatives) as well as on indices (like Sensex & Nifty 50). Circuit breakers are the limits on price movement (on upside & downside) in which the trading of that stock is stopped for sometime to control the volatility in the market. Eg. Circuit breakers on Nifty are placed at 10%, 15% 20%. If these levels are reached within the day, the nationwide trading on all stocks is stopped as per rules. @RohitAshokJorigal f @rohitashokjorigal @RohitAshokJorigal @RohitAshokJorigal'.

text:
AÂ circuit breakerÂ is an automatically operatedÂ electricalÂ switchÂ designed to protect anÂ electrical circuitÂ from damage caused by excess current from an overload orÂ short circuit. Its basic function is to interrupt current flow after a fault is detected. Unlike aÂ fuse, which operates once and then must be replaced, a circuit breaker can be reset (either manually or automatically) to resume normal operation.

Circuit breakers are made in varying sizes, from small devices that protect low-current circuits or individual household appliance, up to largeÂ switchgearÂ designed to protectÂ high voltageÂ circuits feeding an entire city. The generic function of a circuit breaker, orÂ fuse, as an automatic means of removing power from a faulty system is often abbreviated as OCPD (Over Current Protection Device).

It's National Homemade Bread Day tomorrow! ğŸ Letâ€™s celebrate by baking the worldwide favourite: the classic loaf! â 
â 
If youâ€™ve never baked your own, it is the perfect day to taste the deliciousness of a home-made bread using @schar_glutenfree_sg Gluten Free Mix B Bread Mix Flour!Save this recipe for later ğŸ’™ â

500 g Schar Mix B Bread Mix Flourâ 
5 g @salt_odyssey Fine Pure Greek Sea Saltâ

1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oilâ 
400 ml lukewarm waterâ 
â 
ğğ‘ğ„ğğ€ğ‘ğ€ğ“ğˆğğâ â €â 
1. Put the flour and the yeast in a mixing bowl. (Dissolve fresh yeast in lukewarm water; mix dry yeast well with the flour.)â 
2. Add the salt, the oil and water, and then work all of the ingredients into a smooth dough with a spatula.â 
3. Put the dough in a greased bread tin that has been coated with flour, cover with polythene foil or a moist cloth and leave it to rise in a warm place (30Â° C. / 86Â° F.) The dough should approximately double in volume.â 
4. Put the bread in a preheated oven. In order for there to be enough moisture during baking, place a heat-resistant container filled with water on the floor of the oven.â

text:
Today, let's learn from Zhihao for his study tips on Physics Circular Motion! 
-
Hi, I am Zhihao, a graduate from Hwa Chong Institution. I have scored straight A's for A levels (GP, H2 Phy, H2 Math, H2 Econs, H2 Chem) with 90 rank points. As a recent graduate, I can still remember many of the common misconceptions and errors that students will make, and I will work together with the students to correct them. I believe in explaining concepts in a logical and concise manner to make sure that the student can understand the subject fully, instead of just memorising methods to answer questions. As a student, I have received many awards, such as the Outstanding Student Award, Hwa Chong Diploma with Distinction, and the Colours Award. I am currently a part time private tutor teaching mostly H2 physics.

My best friend then was a girl called M. Rubavathi. Then I sat between 2 Indian girls Komala and Thania for 2 years. Oh I grew up staying next to Hindu temple. ğŸ˜† So to all Indian friends whom I have met and interacted with: Happy Diwali!!!

image_desc: Photo by Savannah on November 12, 2020. May be an image of insect.
text:
My love for sensory play started when the lockdown began! S had just turned 2 so I had to explore innovative ways to engage my hyperactive toddler. Unfortunately, we also had to battle the terrible twos phase which emerged around that time! I recall desperately calling up a good friend @skd1983 and confiding in her! Her exact words were, â€œWelcome to the terrible twos phase, my friend.â€ Then it hit me that terrible twos is real but why now? ğŸ¤£

Sâ€™s appetite got worse so I desperately needed a distraction tool. I refused to engage the enemy called iPad further! Most importantly, I felt S needed a new routine, the old one had been disrupted!

Like everyone else, the internet was my window to the world so I researched religiously! And voila! I found sensory play!

I realised sensory play was so easy! Depending on the theme, just throw in a sensory base (rice/chickpeas/water beads), figurines (insects/animals/vehicles) and some tools to dig, sort and scoop or just simply allow the child to explore and discover! 

S responded pretty well which motivated me further! I would first set the scene by preparing an #invitationtoplay tray, at nap time! When she awakes, we go about the usual routine of laying the mat and placing the tray down together! It became our thing! We bonded! At times she gave me orders on what to do which was kinda cute! During situations when I found myself lacking the energy to prepare anything, Iâ€™ll place the sensory materials on the mat and slowly unpack with her! It felt therapeutic! It was our new routine!

During play, when I sense that sheâ€™s highly engaged, Iâ€™ll use the questioning technique to spark her curiosity. Simple qns like â€œDo you know how many legs a spider has?â€ got her thinking and we would start counting together. 

Today sensory play has become a staple at home and go-to option! Itâ€™s been six months, she still reaches for green rice, chickpeas, waterbeads! Sheâ€™s not bored of them yet! I hope she never will be! ğŸ˜…

Any mummies encountered challenges similar to mine during CB? Please do share to let mummies out there know they are not alone! â¤ï¸

text:
Some time in June 2020, I came to accept the fact that my business (@instantly.sg) will not resume back to pre-covid level at least for the rest of the year. With the government not permitting events, my company has been earning $0 in revenue since February. Every day, I will check my bank accounts. Itâ€™s really scary seeing money going out every month, but nothing coming in.
.
.
.
To survive, I know I needed to earn money. I revamped my resume, and applied for numerous full time jobs. But to no avail. With not much options left, I decided to take up a part time job delivering parcels. Every morning, I will collect a bunch of parcels and then deliver them accordingly. For every parcel delivered, I will earn $2.50. On average, I can deliver about 40-60 parcels a day if I work 9-12 hours a day. Thatâ€™s an income of $100 to $150 a day. 
.
.
.
For this job, time is of the essence. The faster I am, the more parcels I can deliver, the more I will earn. Running up and down the blocks became a daily routine. I probably lost a few kg during this period. 
.
.
.
One day, after I delivered a parcel to a woman, she asked me to hold on and donâ€™t leave yet. At the back of my head I was thinking â€œwah lao... what she want? Waste my time...â€. Then, she came back, passed me a drink and $4. She said â€œç»™ä½ å–ã€‚ä»Šå¤©çƒ­ï¼Œå¤šå–æ°´ã€‚è°¢è°¢ä½ å•Š!â€
.
.
.
I kid you not. I literally teared up. Not because I earned an extra $4 and a bottle of drink. But because I felt appreciated and that finally after so long... at least something went right.
.
.
.

This apple and hazelnut cake made with @schar_glutenfree_sg Gluten Free Mix C Patisserie Flour does require quite a bit of preparation before it goes in the oven â€“ but it's definitely worth it! â 
â 
ğˆğğ†ğ‘ğ„ğƒğˆğ„ğğ“ğ’â â €â 
220 g Schar Gluten Free Mix C Patisserie Flourâ 
600 g applesâ 
1 lemonâ 
150 g sugarâ 
125 g butterâ 
3 eggsâ 
1 package baking powderâ 
125 g unsweetened yoghurtâ 
1 pinch/es of  @salt_odyssey Greek Sea Saltâ 
50 g hazelnutsâ 
â 
ğğ‘ğ„ğğ€ğ‘ğ€ğ“ğˆğğâ â €â 
1. Preheat the oven to 180Â°C. Grease a round cake tin (Ã˜ 24 cm) and dust with flour.â 
2. Peel and slice the apples and squeeze some lemon juice over the slices.â 
3. Grind the sugar, hazelnuts and lemon peel in a mixer.â 
4. Place the mixture into a bowl together with the sieved flour, eggs, salt, baking powder, butter and yoghurt and combine this by stirring carefully.â 
5. Place half the mixture into the cake tin and place a layer of apple slices on top.â 
6. Pour the remaining mixture over the top and place another layer of apple slices on top.â 
7. Bake the cake in the centre of the oven for 50 minutes.â

R - 5 mins
W - 3 mins

Lesson learnt, speed walk before training to prevent injury. After training speed walk is to release the additional lactic acid. Don't forget to stretch to prevent muscle cramp.

image_desc: Photo by YuzuğŸ¾Yuki ğŸ‡¸ğŸ‡¬ğŸ‡¯ğŸ‡µ on October 31, 2020. May be an image of cat and text that says 'Birthday T HAPPY'.
text:
ğŸ‚ 1yr old ğŸ‰
Yuzu is nearly 1 year old. We don't know when he was born as no one witnessed. Vet estimated. 

Birthday is a time to reflect one's roots, where one comes from. Yuzu has parents and 3 other siblings including Yuki. The kittens were born in a factory and subsequently found when they were about 6 month old. They were starving and came out of a factory searching for food. A kind lady who feeds community cats fed them everyday until they were transferred to a rehomer. They were put for adoption by #ARKC and we got to know them through July Zoom adoption drive. 

As I reflect how we met with Yuzu&Yuki, we cannot thanks more for kind people who helped along the way without expecting anything back. They truly care for cats wellbeing and give tons of love to any cats they meet. Kudos to all the rescuers&rehomers who put in so much time&effort on daily basis. I thank you, great appreciation to you all on this special occasionğŸ’–ğŸ§¡ğŸ’›
